headline: How Investors Are Reacting To Procter & Gamble (PG) Steady Earnings, Softer Guidance And Flat Organic Sales
summary: In the past week, Procter & Gamble reported fiscal Q2 2026 results showing sales of US$22.21 billion, slightly higher than a year earlier, while net income, basic EPS, and diluted EPS all eased versus the prior period. headline: PG Q4 Deep Dive: Management Cites Innovation and Regional Execution as Key to Growth
summary: Consumer products behemoth Proctor & Gamble (NYSE:PG) met Wall Streets revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025, with sales up 1.5% year on year to $22.21 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.88 per share was 1.2% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: CEOs Wary of a Jittery US Consumer as Global Tensions Intensify
summary: Delta Air Lines Inc. struck a cautious tone on profits amid geopolitical uncertainty, while United Airlines Holdings Inc. warned that global tensions could weigh on travel demand.  Meanwhile, executives at consumer staples giants Procter & Gamble Co. and McCormick & Co. said shoppers remain cautious.  Signs of strain are lingering in industrial sectors as reports from distributor Fastenal Co. and logistics company JB Hunt Transport Services Inc. disappointed investors.

headline: Social Security Faces 24% Benefit Cut in 2032 Without Congressional Action
summary: Social Security faces a fundamental problem that millions of Americans will soon confront directly. The program’s retirement trust fund is projected to deplete by late 2032, just seven years away, according to estimates from the Social Security Chief Actuary.
